<item>
            <title>[CXF-5842] CacheSizeExceededException attachment tempfile leak</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5842</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I set the attachment-max-size option for my endpoint, a CacheSizeExceededException is thrown if the attachment size exceeds the configured value. &lt;br/&gt;
In this case the attachment tempfile is not deleted by the CXF runtime, when I close the AttachmentDataSource InputStream. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Analyzing the issue I noticed that 2 tempfiles are created (I have only 1 attachment), 2 AttachmentDataSource&apos;s can be retreived, but closing both of them deletes only one of the tempfiles.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
